      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "## 12.10 MA(1) spectrum\n",
        "\n",
        "Consider the MA(1) model\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "X_t=W_t+\\theta W_{t-1},\n",
        "\\qquad W_t\\sim WN(0,\\sigma^2).\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "The autocovariance is\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\gamma(h)=\\begin{cases}\n",
        "\\sigma^2(1+\\theta^2), & h=0,\\\\\n",
        "\\sigma^2\\theta, & |h|=1,\\\\\n",
        "0, & |h|>1.\n",
        "\\end{cases}\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Therefore\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\begin{aligned}\n",
        "f(\\omega)\n",
        "&=\\gamma(0)+\\gamma(1)e^{-2\\pi i\\omega}+\\gamma(-1)e^{2\\pi i\\omega}\\\\\n",
        "&=\\sigma^2(1+\\theta^2)+2\\sigma^2\\theta\\cos(2\\pi\\omega)\\\\\n",
        "&=\\sigma^2\\left|1+\\theta e^{-2\\pi i\\omega}\\right|^2.\n",
        "\\end{aligned}\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "If $\\theta>0$, the spectrum is larger at low frequencies. If $\\theta<0$, it is larger near the Nyquist frequency."
      ],
      "id": "8edde270"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: ch12-ma1-spectra\n",
        "#| fig-cap: Theoretical spectral densities for positive and negative MA(1) coefficients.\n",
        "\n",
        "def ma1_spectrum(theta, sigma2=1.0):\n",
        "    return sigma2 * (1 + theta**2 + 2*theta*np.cos(2*np.pi*omega_grid))\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 4))\n",
        "plt.plot(omega_grid, ma1_spectrum(0.9), label=r\"$\\theta=0.9$\")\n",
        "plt.plot(omega_grid, ma1_spectrum(-0.9), label=r\"$\\theta=-0.9$\")\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"frequency\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"spectral density\")\n",
        "plt.title(\"MA(1) spectra\")\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "id": "ch12-ma1-spectra",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
