      "source": [
        "## 12.11 Spectral density of a causal ARMA process\n",
        "\n",
        "Let $X_t$ be a causal ARMA($p,q$) process:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\phi(B)X_t=\\theta(B)W_t,\n",
        "\\qquad W_t\\sim WN(0,\\sigma^2),\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "where\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\phi(B)=1-\\phi_1B-\\cdots-\\phi_pB^p,\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "and\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\theta(B)=1+\\theta_1B+\\cdots+\\theta_qB^q.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Causality gives the linear-process representation\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "X_t=\\psi(B)W_t,\n",
        "\\qquad\n",
        "\\psi(B)=\\frac{\\theta(B)}{\\phi(B)}.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "The spectral density is\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "f(\\omega)\n",
        "=\\sigma^2\\left|\\psi(e^{-2\\pi i\\omega})\\right|^2\n",
        "=\\sigma^2\\frac{\\left|\\theta(e^{-2\\pi i\\omega})\\right|^2}\n",
        "{\\left|\\phi(e^{-2\\pi i\\omega})\\right|^2}.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "This formula is one of the main reasons spectral analysis is useful. ARMA models become simple frequency filters applied to white noise.\n",
        "\n",
        "::: {.callout-note}\n",
        "## ARMA as filtered white noise\n",
        "White noise has a flat spectrum. A causal ARMA model reshapes this flat spectrum by multiplying it by\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\\left|\\frac{\\theta(e^{-2\\pi i\\omega})}{\\phi(e^{-2\\pi i\\omega})}\\right|^2.\n",
        "$$\n",
        "\n",
        "The AR polynomial can amplify frequencies near its roots, while the MA polynomial can suppress or amplify frequencies depending on its zeros.\n",
        ":::"
      ],
      "id": "97887f11"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "#| label: ch12-arma-spectrum-function\n",
        "#| fig-cap: ARMA spectral density computed from the AR and MA polynomials.\n",
        "\n",
        "import numpy.polynomial.polynomial as poly\n",
        "\n",
        "def arma_spectrum(ar_coefs, ma_coefs, sigma2=1.0, grid=None):\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    ar_coefs: [phi_1, ..., phi_p] for phi(B)=1 - phi_1 B - ... - phi_p B^p\n",
        "    ma_coefs: [theta_1, ..., theta_q] for theta(B)=1 + theta_1 B + ... + theta_q B^q\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    if grid is None:\n",
        "        grid = np.linspace(0, 0.5, 400)\n",
        "    z = np.exp(-2j * np.pi * grid)\n",
        "    theta = np.ones_like(z, dtype=complex)\n",
        "    for j, coef in enumerate(ma_coefs, start=1):\n",
        "        theta += coef * z**j\n",
        "    phi = np.ones_like(z, dtype=complex)\n",
        "    for j, coef in enumerate(ar_coefs, start=1):\n",
        "        phi -= coef * z**j\n",
        "    return grid, sigma2 * np.abs(theta)**2 / np.abs(phi)**2\n",
        "\n",
        "freq, spec_a = arma_spectrum(ar_coefs=[1.2, -0.7], ma_coefs=[0.4])\n",
        "freq, spec_b = arma_spectrum(ar_coefs=[0.8], ma_coefs=[-0.8])\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 4))\n",
        "plt.plot(freq, spec_a, label=\"ARMA(2,1)\")\n",
        "plt.plot(freq, spec_b, label=\"ARMA(1,1)\")\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"frequency\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"spectral density\")\n",
        "plt.title(\"ARMA spectra from polynomial ratios\")\n",
        "plt.legend()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "id": "ch12-arma-spectrum-function",
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
